In this post I explore some of the features I&rsquo;m looking forward to in the upcoming JUnit 5 release.
First, a bit of background&hellip;
The process to create a new version of JUnit kicked off around the middle of 2015 when a crowdfunding campaign was started. At this point the initiative was referred to as JUnit Lambda. One of the drivers for this was the release of Java 8 that provided a number of language features, such as Streams and Lambdas, offering new ways for the test framework to be implemented and tests to be written.
